text:
Looking at this task, I need to build a maze game with 24 bots using Tremaux/DFS exploration, smooth rendering, and a precise scripting API. Let me design carefully:

- **Maze**: Recursive backtracking (perfect maze), 21×21
- **Bots**: 24 bots, each with a unique permutation of [N,E,S,W] (24 permutations exist!) for direction preference
- **Exploration**: Tremaux — mark edges as traversed (0→1→2), never traverse mark-2 edges, backtrack when no unmarked edges
- **Determinism**: Seeded RNG, fixed direction orders, no RNG in bot logic
- **Timer**: Freezes when all bots arrived

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Maze Discovery — 24 Bots</title>
<style>
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    font-family: -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
    background: #14142a;
    color: #e8e8f0;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 20px;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }
  h1 { margin: 0 0 12px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; }
  #controls {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 14px;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .stat {
    background: #1f1f3a;
    padding: 6px 12px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid #2e2e55;
  }
  .stat b { color: #8be9fd; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  button {
    padding: 7px 16px;
    background: #4a4af0;
    color: #fff;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: background .15s;
  }
  button:hover { background: #6060ff; }
  button#playpause { background: #2a8a2a; }
  button#playpause:hover { background: #36a336; }
  input[type=range] { vertical-align: middle; }
  #maze {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #0a0a18;
    border: 2px solid #2e2e55;
    border-radius: 4px;
    line-height: 0;
  }
  canvas { display: block; }
  #legend {
    margin-top: 10px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #8888aa;
    max-width: 640px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .swatch {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 10px; height: 10px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin: 0 2px;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Maze Discovery — 24 Bots (Tremaux Exploration)</h1>
<div id="controls">
  <button id="reset">Reset</button>
  <button id="playpause">Pause</button>
  <label>Speed: <input type="range" id="speed" min="2" max="120" value="30"> <span id="speedval">30</span> tps</label>
  <span class="stat">Completed: <b id="completed">0</b>/24</span>
  <span class="stat">Timer: <b id="timer">0</b></span>
  <span class="stat">Last finish: <b id="lastfinish">—</b></span>
</div>
<div id="maze"><canvas id="cv" width="630" height="630"></canvas></div>
<div id="legend">
  Each bot knows only its current cell and learns walls by entering cells. Bots explore via Tremaux/DFS:
  they take unmarked passages (preferring their unique direction order), backtrack at dead ends, mark
  branches dead, and never traverse a passage more than twice. No global pathfinding is used.
  <span class="swatch" style="background:#2a6a2a"></span> Spawn
  <span class="swatch" style="background:#b8860b"></span> Exit
</div>

<script>
"use strict";

const ROWS = 21, COLS = 21;
const CELL = 30;
const NUM_BOTS = 24;

let maze, spawn, exitPos, bots, elapsed;
let playing = true;
let ticksPerSec = 30;
let acc = 0, lastTime = 0;

/* ---------- Seeded RNG (mulberry32) ---------- */
function mulberry32(a) {
  return function() {
    a |= 0; a = (a + 0x6D2B79F5) | 0;
    let t = Math.imul(a ^ (a >>> 15), 1 | a);
    t = (t + Math.imul(t ^ (t >>> 7), 61 | t)) ^ t;
    return ((t ^ (t >>> 14)) >>> 0) / 4294967296;
  };
}

/* ---------- Perfect maze via recursive backtracking ---------- */
function generateMaze(rows, cols, seed) {
  const rng = mulberry32(seed);
  const cells = [];
  for (let r = 0; r < rows; r++) {
    cells[r] = [];
    for (let c = 0; c < cols; c++) {
      cells[r][c] = { n: true, e: true, s: true, w: true, visited: false };
    }
  }
  const stack = [{ r: 0, c: 0 }];
  cells[0][0].visited = true;
  while (stack.length) {
    const cur = stack[stack.length - 1];
    const ns = [];
    if (cur.r > 0 && !cells[cur.r - 1][cur.c].visited) ns.push({ r: cur.r - 1, c: cur.c, dir: 'n' });
    if (cur.c < cols - 1 && !cells[cur.r][cur.c + 1].visited) ns.push({ r: cur.r, c: cur.c + 1, dir: 'e' });
    if (cur.r < rows - 1 && !cells[cur.r + 1][cur.c].visited) ns.push({ r: cur.r + 1, c: cur.c, dir: 's' });
    if (cur.c > 0 && !cells[cur.r][cur.c - 1].visited) ns.push({ r: cur.r, c: cur.c - 1, dir: 'w' });
    if (!ns.length) { stack.pop(); continue; }
    const nx = ns[Math.floor(rng() * ns.length)];
    if (nx.dir === 'n') { cells[cur.r][cur.c].n = false; cells[nx.r][nx.c].s = false; }
    else if (nx.dir === 'e') { cells[cur.r][cur.c].e = false; cells[nx.r][nx.c].w = false; }
    else if (nx.dir === 's') { cells[cur.r][cur.c].s = false; cells[nx.r][nx.c].n = false; }
    else { cells[cur.r][cur.c].w = false; cells[nx.r][nx.c].e = false; }
    cells[nx.r][nx.c].visited = true;
    stack.push(nx);
  }
  return cells;
}

/* ---------- All 24 permutations of [N,E,S,W] ---------- */
function permutations(arr) {
  if (arr.length <= 1) return [arr.slice()];
  const res = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    const rest = arr.slice(0, i).concat(arr.slice(i + 1));
    for (const p of permutations(rest)) res.push([arr[i]].concat(p));
  }
  return res;
}
const DIR_ORDERS = permutations(['n', 'e', 's', 'w']); // length 24

/* ---------- Bot creation ---------- */
function makeBots() {
  const arr = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < NUM_BOTS; i++) {
    arr.push({
      id: i,
      dirOrder: DIR_ORDERS[i],
      r: spawn.r,
      c: spawn.c,
      visR: spawn.r,
      visC: spawn.c,
      path: [{ r: spawn.r, c: spawn.c }],
      deadEnds: [],
      finishTick: null,
      arrived: false,
      // internal memory (local knowledge only)
      knownWalls: Object.create(null),
      edgeMarks: Object.create(null),
      stack: []
    });
  }
  return arr;
}

function edgeKey(r1, c1, r2, c2) {
  if (r1 < r2 || (r1 === r2 && c1 < c2)) return r1 + ',' + c1 + '|' + r2 + ',' + c2;
  return r2 + ',' + c2 + '|' + r1 + ',' + c1;
}

/* ---------- One Tremaux step for a bot (local knowledge only) ---------- */
function stepBot(bot) {
  if (bot.arrived) return;
  const ck = bot.r + ',' + bot.c;
  if (!bot.knownWalls[ck]) {
    // Learn this cell's walls by being here (local sensing)
    const w = maze[bot.r][bot.c];
    bot.knownWalls[ck] = { n: w.n, e: w.e, s: w.s, w: w.w };
  }
  const walls = bot.knownWalls[ck];

  // Look for an unmarked passable edge, in this bot's preferred direction order
  let chosen = null;
  for (const d of bot.dirOrder) {
    let nr = bot.r, nc = bot.c;
    if (d === 'n') nr--; else if (d === 'e') nc++; else if (d === 's') nr++; else nc--;
    if (nr < 0 || nr >= ROWS || nc < 0 || nc >= COLS) continue;
    if (walls[d]) continue; // there is a wall
    const ek = edgeKey(bot.r, bot.c, nr, nc);
    const mark = bot.edgeMarks[ek] || 0;
    if (mark === 0) { chosen = { nr, nc, ek }; break; }
  }

  if (chosen) {
    // Forward: traverse unmarked passage (0 -> 1)
    bot.edgeMarks[chosen.ek] = 1;
    bot.stack.push({ r: bot.r, c: bot.c });
    bot.r = chosen.nr;
    bot.c = chosen.nc;
    bot.path.push({ r: bot.r, c: bot.c });
  } else {
    // No unmarked passage: backtrack along the edge we came from (1 -> 2)
    if (bot.stack.length === 0) return; // fully explored (shouldn't happen before exit found)
    const prev = bot.stack.pop();
    const ek = edgeKey(bot.r, bot.c, prev.r, prev.c);
    bot.edgeMarks[ek] = (bot.edgeMarks[ek] || 0) + 1; // becomes 2
    bot.deadEnds.push({ r: bot.r, c: bot.c });
    bot.r = prev.r;
    bot.c = prev.c;
    bot.path.push({ r: bot.r, c: bot.c });
  }
}

/* ---------- Tick (deterministic) ---------- */
function tick(n) {
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    if (bots.every(b => b.arrived)) break; // freeze: no further state changes
    elapsed++;
    for (const bot of bots) {
      stepBot(bot);
      if (!bot.arrived && bot.r === exitPos.r && bot.c === exitPos.c) {
        bot.arrived = true;
        bot.finishTick = elapsed;
      }
    }
  }
  updateUI();
}

/* ---------- Reset ---------- */
function reset(seed) {
  if (seed === undefined) seed = Math.floor(Math.random() * 1e9);
  maze = generateMaze(ROWS, COLS, seed >>> 0);
  spawn = { r: 0, c: 0 };
  exitPos = { r: ROWS - 1, c: COLS - 1 };
  bots = makeBots();
  elapsed = 0;
  updateUI();
}

function updateUI() {
  const done = bots.filter(b => b.arrived).length;
  document.getElementById('completed').textContent = done;
  document.getElementById('timer').textContent = elapsed;
  const lastFinish = Math.max(0, ...bots.map(b => b.finishTick || 0));
  document.getElementById('lastfinish').textContent = lastFinish || '—';
}

/* ---------- Rendering ---------- */
const cv = document.getElementById('cv');
const ctx = cv.getContext('2d');
cv.width = COLS * CELL;
cv.height = ROWS * CELL;

function botColor(i) {
  // Golden-ratio hue spacing for visual distinctness
  const hue = (i * 137.508) % 360;
  return `hsl(${hue.toFixed(1)},75%,62%)`;
}

let pulseT = 0;

function render(ts) {
  pulseT = (ts || 0) * 0.001;
  ctx.fillStyle = '#0a0a18';
  ctx.fillRect(0, 0, cv.width, cv.height);

  // Spawn cell
  ctx.fillStyle = '#2a6a2a';
  ctx.fillRect(spawn.c * CELL, spawn.r * CELL, CELL, CELL);

  // Exit cell with pulse
  const pulse = 0.5 + 0.5 * Math.sin(pulseT * 3);
  ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(184,134,11,${0.55 + 0.35 * pulse})`;
  ctx.fillRect(exitPos.c * CELL, exitPos.r * CELL, CELL, CELL);
  ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,215,0,${0.6 + 0.4 * pulse})`;
  ctx.lineWidth = 2;
  ctx.strokeRect(exitPos.c * CELL + 1, exitPos.r * CELL + 1, CELL - 2, CELL - 2);

  // Faint overlay of all dead-end cells (exploration progress)
  ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(255,80,80,0.06)';
  for (const bot of bots) {
    for (const d of bot.deadEnds) {
      ctx.fillRect(d.c * CELL, d.r * CELL, CELL, CELL);
    }
  }

  // Walls
  ctx.strokeStyle = '#5566aa';
  ctx.lineWidth = 2;
  ctx.lineCap = 'square';
  ctx.beginPath();
  for (let r = 0; r < ROWS; r++) {
    for (let c = 0; c < COLS; c++) {
      const w = maze[r][c];
      const x = c * CELL, y = r * CELL;
      if (w.n) { ctx.moveTo(x, y); ctx.lineTo(x + CELL, y); }
      if (w.w) { ctx.moveTo(x, y); ctx.lineTo(x, y + CELL); }
      if (r === ROWS - 1 && w.s) { ctx.moveTo(x, y + CELL); ctx.lineTo(x + CELL, y + CELL); }
      if (c === COLS - 1 && w.e) { ctx.moveTo(x + CELL, y); ctx.lineTo(x + CELL, y + CELL); }
    }
  }
  ctx.stroke();

  // Bots (smoothly interpolated visual position)
  for (const bot of bots) {
    // Ease visual position toward logical position
    bot.visR += (bot.r - bot.visR) * 0.28;
    bot.visC += (bot.c - bot.visC) * 0.28;
    const x = bot.visC * CELL + CELL / 2;
    const y = bot.visR * CELL + CELL / 2;
    const radius = CELL * 0.3;
    // glow for arrived bots
    if (bot.arrived) {
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(120,255,150,0.25)';
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(x, y, radius * 1.6, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fill();
    }
    ctx.fillStyle = botColor(bot.id);
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.arc(x, y, radius, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.fill();
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.55)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;
    ctx.stroke();
    // id label
    ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.7)';
    ctx.font = 'bold 9px monospace';
    ctx.textAlign = 'center';
    ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';
    ctx.fillText(bot.id, x, y);
  }

  requestAnimationFrame(render);
}

/* ---------- Auto-play loop ---------- */
function loop(t) {
  if (!lastTime) lastTime = t;
  const dt = t - lastTime;
  lastTime = t;
  if (playing) {
    acc += dt;
    const interval = 1000 / ticksPerSec;
    let guard = 0;
    while (acc >= interval && guard < 1000) {
      acc -= interval;
      tick(1);
      guard++;
      if (bots.every(b => b.arrived)) { playing = false; document.getElementById('playpause').textContent = 'Play'; break; }
    }
  }
  requestAnimationFrame(loop);
}

/* ---------- Init ---------- */
reset(Math.floor(Math.random() * 1e9));
requestAnimationFrame(render);
requestAnimationFrame(loop);

/* ---------- UI controls ---------- */
document.getElementById('reset').onclick = () => {
  reset(Math.floor(Math.random() * 1e9));
  playing = true;
  document.getElementById('playpause').textContent = 'Pause';
};
document.getElementById('playpause').onclick = function () {
  if (bots.every(b => b.arrived)) return; // nothing to play
  playing = !playing;
  this.textContent = playing ? 'Pause' : 'Play';
};
const speedEl = document.getElementById('speed');
const speedVal = document.getElementById('speedval');
speedEl.oninput = function () {
  ticksPerSec = parseInt(this.value, 10);
  speedVal.textContent = ticksPerSec;
};

/* ---------- Scripting API ---------- */
window.game = {
  tick: function (n) { tick(n | 0); },
  reset: function (seed) { reset(seed); },
  get elapsed() { return elapsed; },
  get size() { return { rows: ROWS, cols: COLS }; },
  get spawn() { return { r: spawn.r, c: spawn.c }; },
  get exit() { return { r: exitPos.r, c: exitPos.c }; },
  walls: function (r, c) {
    const w = maze[r][c];
    return { n: w.n, e: w.e, s: w.s, w: w.w };
  },
  get bots() { return bots; }
};
</script>
</body>
</html>
```

**How it works:**

- **Maze generation**: Recursive backtracking with a seeded mulberry32 RNG produces a perfect maze (spanning tree, fully connected, no loops). Same seed → identical maze.

- **Bot exploration (Tremaux/DFS)**: Each bot maintains local memory only — `knownWalls` (learned by entering cells) and `edgeMarks` (how many times each passage has been traversed). Each tick a bot:
  1. Senses its current cell's walls (local knowledge only — no global map).
  2. Looks for an unmarked passable edge (mark 0) in its **unique direction preference order** (one of the 24 permutations of N/E/S/W). If found, traverse it (mark 0→1).
  3. Otherwise backtrack along the edge it came from (mark 1→2), recording the departed cell in `deadEnds`.
  4. Never traverses a mark-2 edge → **no passage traversed more than twice**.

- **No global pathfinding**: Bots never see the full maze. They spread out because each has a distinct direction order.

- **Determinism**: `tick(n)` loops `n` times over deterministic `stepBot` calls, so `tick(1)`×n ≡ `tick(n)`. No RNG in bot logic.

- **Timer freeze**: `tick` breaks immediately if all bots have arrived, so `elapsed` and bot state never change after the last arrival.

- **Rendering**: Canvas 630×630. Walls drawn per-cell. Bots are colored dots (golden-ratio hue spacing) with smoothly eased visual positions (`visR/visC` lerp toward logical `r/c`), centered in corridors. Exit pulses; arrived bots get a green glow; dead-end cells show faint red.

- **API**: `window.game` exposes `tick`, `reset`, `elapsed`, `size`, `spawn`, `exit`, `walls`, and `bots` (each with `path`, `deadEnds`, `finishTick`). All 24 bots finish well within 20,000 ticks (max ~2×(441−1)=880 traversals per bot).
